[30;1m109 | [0m[35mdef build_unit_tree(store, filename=None):[0m
[30;1m110 | [0m[35m    """[0m
[30;1m111 | [0m[35m    Enumerate a translation store and build a tree with XPath components as nodes[0m
[30;1m112 | [0m[35m    and where a node contains a unit if a path from the root of the tree to the node[0m
[30;1m113 | [0m[35m    containing the unit, is equal to the XPath of the unit.[0m
[30;1m114 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m115 | [0m[35m    The tree looks something like this::[0m
[30;1m116 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m567[0m[34m of [0m[33m2013[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/translate_toolkit-3.15.1/translate/storage/xml_extract/unit_tree.py[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m109 | [0m[35mdef build_unit_tree(store, filename=None):[0m
[30;1m110 | [0m[35m    """[0m
[30;1m111 | [0m[35m    Enumerate a translation store and build a tree with XPath components as nodes[0m
[30;1m112 | [0m[35m    and where a node contains a unit if a path from the root of the tree to the node[0m
[30;1m113 | [0m[35m    containing the unit, is equal to the XPath of the unit.[0m
[30;1m114 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m10 | [0m[35mEscaping -- DTD files are no longer escaped[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35m-------------------------------------------[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35mPreviously each converter handled escaping, which made it a nightmare every[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35mtime we identified an escaping related error or added a new format.  Escaping[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35mhas now been moved into the format classes as much as possible, the result[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35mbeing that formats exchange Python strings and manage their own escaping.[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m502 | [0m[35m	(cd $returndir; find . -type f -name "*.po" | sort ) > $returnlist[0m
[30;1m503 | [0m[35m	echo "Reviews out: `cat $reviewlist | wc -l`"[0m

[30;1m86 | [0m[35mOne strategy is to run each test individually.  This allows you to focus on one[0m
[30;1m87 | [0m[35mproblem at a time across a number of files.  It is much easier to correct end[0m
[30;1m88 | [0m[35mpunctuation on its own then to correct many different types of errors.  For a[0m

[30;1m99 | [0m[35m* If everything matches we carry that across[0m

[30;1m105 | [0m[35m  algorithm to detect the best matches[0m

[30;1m20 | [0m[35mA workflow is defined by a set of states that a translation unit can be in and[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35mthe (allowed) transitions between these states. A state is defined by a range[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35mbetween -128 and 127, indicating its level of "completeness". The range is[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35mclosed at the beginning and open at the end. That is, if a workflow contains[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35mstates A, B and C where A < B < C, a unit with state number n is in state A if[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35mA <= n < B, state B if B <= n < C or state C if C <= n < MAX.[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m194 | [0m[35mdef _build_translated_dom(dom_node, target_node, target_dom_to_doc_dom):[0m

[30;1m111 | [0m[35mtranslation in ``lang/zu`` we create a set of PO files in ``po-zu``.  These[0m

[30;1m113 | [0m[35m100% you need to have both English and Zulu at the same revision, if they are[0m
[30;1m114 | [0m[35mnot you will have to review all translations.[0m
[30;1m115 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m116 | [0m[35mYou are now in a position to translate your recovered translations or your new[0m

[30;1m92 | [0m[35mExamples[0m
[30;1m93 | [0m[35m========[0m
[30;1m94 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m95 | [0m[35mThis example looks at roundtrip of flat XML translations as well as recovery of[0m
[30;1m96 | [0m[35mexisting translations.[0m
[30;1m97 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m98 | [0m[35mFirst we need to create a set of POT files.::[0m

[30;1m102 | [0m[35mAll .xml files found in the ``lang/en`` directory are converted to Gettext POT[0m
